      <div class="post post-761 type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-deans-perspectives tag-aavmc tag-education tag-leadership tag-veterinary-medicine" id="post-761">
       <div class="post-inner">
        <div class="post-header">
         <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/2019/03/05/inspiring-action-through-leadership/">
           Inspiring Action Through Leadership
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="post-meta">
          <p class="post-author">
           <span>
            By
           </span>
           <a href="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/author/mlairmor/" rel="author" title="Posts by Michael Lairmore">
            Michael Lairmore
           </a>
          </p>
          <p class="post-date">
           <span>
            On
           </span>
           <a href="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/2019/03/05/inspiring-action-through-leadership/">
            March 5, 2019
           </a>
          </p>
          <p class="post-categories">
           <span>
            In
           </span>
           <a href="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/category/deans-perspectives/" rel="category tag">
            Dean's Perspectives
           </a>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .post-header -->
        <div class="post-content">
         <p>
          <em>
           “If your actions inspire others to dream more, learn more, do more and become more, you are a leader.”
          </em>
          – John Quincy Adams
         </p>
         <div class="wp-caption alignleft" id="attachment_764" style="width: 639px">
          <a href="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A.jpg">
           <img alt="" class="wp-image-764 size-large" height="418" sizes="(max-width: 629px) 100vw, 629px" src="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A-1024x680.jpg" srcset="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A-1024x680.jpg 1024w, https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A-300x199.jpg 300w, https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A-768x510.jpg 768w, https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A-900x598.jpg 900w, https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/205/2019/03/Lairmore-in-front-of-3A-1280x850.jpg 1280w" width="629"/>
          </a>
          <p class="wp-caption-text">
           Dean Michael Lairmore assumes role of President of AAVMC in March.
          </p>
         </div>
         <p>
          This week I have the distinct privilege to be appointed as President of the
          <a href="https://www.aavmc.org/">
           American Association of Veterinary Medical Colleges
          </a>
          (AAVMC), during the association’s annual conference in Washington, D.C. The conference will focus on “
          <em>
           The Science of Building Inclusive Teams,
          </em>
          ” to promote more effective group decision-making and organizational development.
         </p>
         <p>
          The mission of the AAVMC is parallel to the School’s mission, through the promotion of health of people, animals and the environment by advancing the profession and the education of veterinary students to meet the needs of a changing world. In assuming a leadership position in this organization, I am proud to represent the values, aspirations, and goals of our School beyond UC Davis.
         </p>
         <p>
          <a class="more-link" href="https://lairvet.faculty.ucdavis.edu/2019/03/05/inspiring-action-through-leadership/">
           Read More
          </a>
         </p>
         <div class="rtsocial-container rtsocial-container-align-center rtsocial-icon">
